    "A mutation step was triggered if the effective sample size (6) fell below 400 (γ = 0.4).",
    "Updating of N was triggered following a move step if the estimate σ2",
    "enkf,t (y 0:t |x 1:N 0:t)] exceeded 1.5, resulting in the update Ñ = σ2",
    "We additionally ran NEnKF with a delayed acceptance kernel in the move step, based on the k-nearest neighbours surrogate of Section 4.2, with k = 3.",
    "This gave a modest decrease in CPU time of around 10% over NEnKF; therefore all results are based on NEnKF with delayed acceptance."
